# The revolutionary movement of the proletariat advanced by waves

Author: carga

Time: 2023-03-01T73:00:00-04:00

Head Description: We reproduce the second part of the introduction to the PCR program, approved in its 13th Congress, held in October 2022.

Description: Subsequently, after the capitalist restoration in the USSR (1957) Mao Tsetung: he takes up and develops the conception elaborated by Lenin, pointing out that: “The socialist society covers a fairly long historical stage; Throughout this historical stage, even after fundamentally fulfilling the socialist transformation of the property system on the media & Hellip;

Images: ['[PCR-Banderas.jpg](https://pcr.org.ar/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/PCR-Banderas.jpg)', '[Columna-pcr-24-de-marzo-2019-CABA-300x167.jpg](http://pcr.org.ar/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Columna-pcr-24-de-marzo-2019-CABA-300x167.jpg)']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T73-00-00-04-00/PCR-Banderas.jpg)Subsequently, after capitalist restoration in the USSR(1957)Maotsetung: Retakes and develops the conception elaborated by Lenin, pointing out that: “Socialist society covers a fairly long historical stage; During all this historical stage, even after fundamentally fulfilled socialist transformation of the property system on the media, there are still both classes and the contradictions to be said and the class struggle; There is the struggle between the socialist and capitalist path; There is the danger of capitalist restoration and there is threat subversion and aggression by imperialism and social -imperialism. ”

Learning from the Soviet experience Mao Tsetung promoted in China a gigigant revolution aimed at recovering the positions of power in the hands of the revisionists.

The Chinese proletarian cultural revolution was a great revolution starring millions of men and women, young and old, workers, peasants, students, etc., which from 1966 moved that country and the world. With it, it was possible to prevent capitalist restoration and sustain the dictatorship of the proletarian for more than ten years, taking it to its most advanced point.

With the defeat of the proletarian cultural revolution after death, Demando Tsetung and other leaders of the Communist Party of China, and with capitalist larestouration in China, in 1978, ** a stage ** was closed ** in the development of the revolutionary movement of the world proletariat ; A stage in which the proletariat conquered and exercised power in countries that arrived covering the third part of humanity and great conquests were achieved.

Since its origins, the revolutionary movement of the proletariat advanced by him and suffered losses and large bleeding, but none of these had the lamagnitude of the capitalist restoration in the socialist countries. It was a defeat for the proletariat and the oppressed peoples. A historical true.The struggle to end forever with the exploitation of man by man will lead a long historical process. Sometimes it will seem that the exploiters, the reacted ones, are invincible; others, that the massive mass movement.

“How different are the logic of imperialism and that of the people!Provocardisturbs, fail, provoke riots again, fail again, and thus the ruin: this is the logic of the imperialists and all the surroundings of the world in the face of the cause of the people, and they will not march against this logic. This is a Marxist law.(…)Fight, fail, fight again, fail again, fight again, and so on to wash: this is the logic of the people, which will never march in contrade. This is another Marxist law. "(Mao Tsetung: ** "Discard illusions, prepare for the fight" **).

Es imposible defender el comunismo y enfrentar el revisionismo sin enarbolarla verdadera doctrina de Marx y Engels, sin defender los desarrollos a partirde las enseñanzas de validez universal que aportaron las revolucionestriunfantes del siglo XX. Los aportes de Lenin, en particular a la filosofíamarxista, a las teorías de la hegemonía proletaria en la revolucióndemocrática, del imperialismo, del Estado y del partido revolucionario. Y sinreivindicar los aportes de Mao Tsetung, especialmente a la filosofía marxista,a las teorías sobre la revolución de nueva democracia en los países oprimidos,de la guerra revolucionaria, del partido revolucionario, del Estado; y sinreivindicar la Revolución Cultural Proletaria China y la teoría sobre lacontinuación de la revolución en las condiciones de la dictadura delproletariado, aporte fundamental de Mao Tsetung al desarrollo del marxismo.Esto es necesario para defender la teoría marxista frente al revisionismo yasí se podrá integrarla con la realidad de cada país, desarrollar esa mismateoría y abordar los nuevos problemas del movimiento revolucionario en elsiglo XXI. Sólo así se puede enfrentar exitosamente los embates de la reaccióny el revisionismo, que niegan los logros del socialismo y siembran elescepticismo sobre toda posibilidad de cambio revolucionario y el logro delobjetivo histórico de la clase obrera: una sociedad sin explotadores niexplotados, el comunismo.

Con el marxismo-leninismo-maoísmo como guía nos nutrimos de la historia delucha de la clase obrera y del pueblo argentino que han bocetado una y otravez el camino insurreccional.



[![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T73-00-00-04-00/Columna-pcr-24-de-marzo-2019-CABA-300x167.jpg)](http://pcr.org.ar/nota/el-movimiento-revolucionario-del-proletariado-avanzo-por-oleadas/columna-pcr-24-de-marzo-2019-caba-2/)Today N ° 1952 03/01/2023

News Source: [https://pcr.org.ar/nota/el-movimiento-revolucionario-del-proletariado-avanzo-por-oleadas/](https://pcr.org.ar/nota/el-movimiento-revolucionario-del-proletariado-avanzo-por-oleadas/)

