Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T77-00-00-04-00/Perú.jpg)Companion Almejún tells us that this mission was carried out “in the face of the reports of human rights violations in the Hermanarepublic and the request for observation and verification, an invitation to be that form human rights organizations comoliberpueblo and Xumek, social and popular organizations such as the Patriagrande Front, front of organizations in struggle, popular movement dignity, piquetero party, religious groups such as the group of priests in the option by the poor, union organizations such as Sipreba, Ate and Cta-autonoma ”.

On the objectives set, he states: “Relieve the situations of violation of the human rights within the framework of the popular lifting due to the existing political and social crisis. Prepare a preliminary report that accounts for immediate results. Prepare a final report that makes visible the temples and denunciations at national and international level, contribute to a regional defense articulation promoting and protecting Human Rights in order to eliminate the repressive action of the current regime. ”

Almejún says that in Peru “we divide into work groups and we have to the most affected regions such as: Juliaca, Ica, Cusco, Ayacucho and Lima. This allowed us to directly listen to the voice of Las Víctimas and their relatives and organizations and organizations of the different regions of the country.

“There is a systematic action of both the Armed Forces and security entrust the territory. The disproportionate abuse of deadly weapons that caused the physical injuries of the participants of the manifestations. Gas, gas, smoke, stamped, tanks, concentration of large numbers of officials harassing the inhabitants. Constant use of lead bullets and short distance and lethal points of the body.

Tanks were used in the operation carried out at the University of Sanmarcos against students and professors and there were sexual abuse against women.#### ** An indiscriminate repression **

Fernando says that the main victims of indiscriminate representation “The popular sectors, especially the periphery of the great city that expressed great discontent. They blocked routes and streets. The Mayoritarians were groups of indigenous and peasants of the different regions and they were added the population of Lima.

The Ronderos, a characteristic form of peasant organization that collaborates in different jurisdictions of communities and youth in the cities, have been a special objective of repressive forces.

“Women are central to the conflict. From the support, care, food and shelter of provincials, those that participate in the demonstrations have been victims of second. The indigenous people suffered racism and supremacism in addition to the common of refressive acts. ”

Liberpueblo's lawyer also says that “people perceive that institutions do nothing to protect their rights and are generally used emergency configures to justify violations and violations of constitutional Lasgarants. The media act by making protest or stigmatizing ethnic and political groups.

“In Ayacucho we were received by Fredepa(Defense Front of the People of Ayacucho), which have been carried out since 1969 a basic work providing social, health and food services. They contacted us relatives of Las Víctimas de la Massacre held on December 15, 2022 by the Army and the National Police. It occurred when a peaceful demonstration was directed by the city center to the airport. In that area the public forces initiated the repression where 9 people lost their lives and there were 72 wounded, 45 gravity. Some of them did not participate in the march. They murdered a 15 -year -old boy, as well as a man who helped still injured.

“In Juliaca we interviewed relatives of 15 of the 18 killed on January 9, almost all of them with mortal shots and wounded at least 204 people of which 61 received ammunition of firearms.

"As noted by lawyers who defend relatives of detainees, the judicial power decided that they are the prosecutors specialized in organized crime" who intervene in the ongoing conflicts in Peru.“In Lima, the mission met with the National Agrarian Confederation and Directors of Peasant Communities. Contact was made with victims that on January 21 were at the University of San Marcos, where 208 people arrested illegally.

The Central of Workers of Peru and the CUT was attended and the 9 Deprbrane the complete mission participated in the march that was made in the Marcodel National unemployment convened by the workers' centrals and different social and political organizations, ”concludes Almejún.

Today N ° 1952 03/01/2023

