<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T83-00-00-04-00/Mujeres-originarias.jpg)Sol begins by framing the current situation of the original women “the sisters of the different villages from the more than 40 pre -existing nations of the State that are still being developed today in ourpaís, understand that more than 530 years of colonial oppression, we continue with Lamisma state oppression, the overwhelming of our traditional and community lives. ” Our interviewee raises that labor exploitation, generation after generation, has impoverished to native and native. that to this day they are patent and even were transferred to the organization of our peoples and our own brothers and sisters. That is not something that has happened to us by the side.

“We have racial and class exploitation, because we are workers and champions, we are originally and the exploitation for being women. In that is a latency of genocide to our native peoples and nevertheless knowledge and our form of organization. We are the women in our communities, which we have a role of knowledge, the care of our territories, of the social organization, but also, laconexion with our territories and respect for all the forces that compose our territories. And this is not poetic or spiritual, the women who put the body, as seen in the brutal repression of la chanomunity in Bariloche, where the dams were all women. There is a message. There is no intention to raise the role of the native peoples in the decisions of our country. ”

#### ** The experience of an urban community **Sol counts the process of identifying the Mapuche problem in a urban center, because “so far there was a very exclusive reading for rurality and awarding the indigenous identity always in rurality and always and when they have a legal status or have a determined territory, they can develop ” For this, it helped her to participate in the meetings of native peoples and nations and from there follow the fight of "the villages by free self -determination and the self -determination of our economic, political, social development, etc.".

Our interviewee says that they are in the process constituting unacomunidad(lof)Urban, Newen Ko Ka Mapu, and from there follow the struggle for territorial reference, Law 26,160 “Against dispossession, Deviolence exercise in the bodies of the sisters, and everything that makes our culture identity. We learned that in college should also be fought for thoseteritories and for the recognition of the preexistence of the hundreds that inhabit, which are part of a pre -existing people to the State and that correspond specific legal rights.

“When we talk about the specificity of territorial rights and banners we also have to understand that when there is racial oppression and decrease, it is even deeper in women originating due to their sermujer status and because in the exercise of these violence it continues with a gag more than 530 years and that different modes of state continued to provide,

“We understand that when there is emergency in violence against women, it is still in original women. Until we are granted our free development as a pre -existing people and we walk to a plurinational state, vain to continue talking about native women as objects of study, and noticing protagonists, subjects of our own rights, because we are nosters who put the body in our territories , and for example in pandemic, were the indigenous people, the first to head the emergency groups as a result of the deepest needs. ”

And Sol adds that this did it based on "the form of organization of the original people, which is community", highlighting the prominence in struggles "headed by native women, who are still imposed by patriarchal uniolence."Today N ° 1952 03/01/2023

