The National MIJP-CCC coordinator and member of the Central PCR Committee, Mariano Sánchez, ratified that “we have been fighting the adjustment. And let's get an increase that takes us out of the indigence line, we do not want to spend the increase are bonds. The other issue is that the expansion of the moratorium is locked, which affects about 800 thousand people of age, and we claim that the moratorium will be extended. We have planted it years ago. A person who loses his job around 50 years, is very difficult for him to be inserted again in the labor market, and therefore does not have the necessary contributions to retire. And the other issue is situation in the Pami, which is the social work of retirees and pensioners, and is not in the hands of their owners. It has been intervened for years. Then all the problems are maintained, that the medical shifts delay and the colleagues die, that they do not provide essential medicines as pressure, for example. And we also went to the ANMAT, because they have made food delivery, which are not fulfilled, ”said Sánchez.

#### **White Bay**

On the same 24 we mobilize almost 100 retirees and pensioners from the MIJP to Ansesde Bay where we claim, as the regional leader Noraalfaro told the media “due Together with the claim that we are in the country, we tell those Congressmen of the PRO that they do not play with us, they have paralyzed the pension moratorium that makes about 4 thousand that they cannot retire in Bahíahaya.

