Description: The companion Valeria begins by framing the situation in the shipyard, where “we have a fairly complicated situation. We are practically standing, waiting if we can sign any employment contract for this year ”, which she considers complicated taking into account that" we have the presidential elections, and that everyone's front is not very consolidated. There is discontent. Se & Hellip;

