![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T95-00-00-04-00/Trabajadoras-del-ARS.jpg)** The companion Valeria begins by framing the situation in the shipyard **, where “we have a very complicated situation. We are practicallyparated, waiting if we can sign any employment contract for this year ”, which she considers complicated taking into account that" we have the presidential elections, and that everyone's front is not very consolidated. HaydesContento. It is understood that all this comes from drag. This government, after we fight so much to win, to close to the right, noted time to govern that they already fell a pandemic. ” The companion states that “we are not at a very good general moment in the factory. Not because of the workmen, but unfortunately, there are no political decisions to Favordel Astillero. Now they go out from the Inidep(National Institute for Fisheries Research and Development)who want to buy the ships outside, when we have the shipyards standing. That is why the situation is complicated. We will do our best so as not to go back. But if this happens, all the companions of the shipyard have it clear that we are the main center that stayed with the desire to dynamit it. ”

On the situation of the workers, the first thing Valeria counts is that “although some workers entered, during the pandemic and then, even eagles from the Astillero Technical School, as others retired, we continue to be between 350 and 400 the women we worked In the shipyard. We are fighting so that the companions who enter, or those who are already, seize going to production.

“We have advanced in very small steps so that partners join direct aproduction. That is, working above the ship, in the workshops, nobators, not doing administrative work within the workshop. We have welding companions, in repair in dike, mechanics, enlistment, winding, mechanical maintenance. The companies that are in production are still minimal. The bulk is in the administrative part and services, in the garden, the school, the nursing, etc.

“We were also advancing in the fight to put into operation, the year, the protocol against violence within the shipyard, along with interdisciplinary unaccius.#### **Working conditions**

On working conditions, the partner tells us that “the salary is aimed at that of the companions, but there is a difference when reaching unacategory, a management position, area head, or supervisor. For last year, almost ending the year, two 18 -year -old partners and the Ortracon 19 in the company managed to have the supervision category. This was for a fight of the classmates. The same colleagues in the area were unemployed in the sector to grant them the category and do not bring a DeAfuera supervisor.

“The claim of the companions, more than anything, is access to the categories, which is the same for men and women. We fight against the evidence.

On whether they have any specific organization of the workers, Valeria says that “we have the gender delegates, that we chose any other partner, like any other sector of the shipyard. This is implemented since 2006, and the number of delegates is according to the lacanity of companions who are in the factory. That is why we have a four -year gender in the body of delegates. ”

On March 8, Valeria says that they are in the preparations, the delegates are mainly responsible for what the delegates are mainly responsible. "What we do all years is to adhere to unemployment, and we also join the march that has been here in La Plata." Finally, says the companion who are preparing for an activity that is done every year at the initiative of the Women's Ministry of the Province of Buenos Aires. It is made on March 11 in San Martín Plaza, and the women of the shipyard we put a stand. There we are the manual that we assemble in the factory to dictate what does to the law, and also deliver specimens of “women who make ships”, the liber made by the women of the shipyard. This is part of what we do all the days to continue trying to change the reality of the factory women. ”

