# Streets on March 8!

Author: lipunkantaja

Time: 2023-03-01T99:00:00-04:00

Images: ['[8323.png](https://punalippu.noblogs.org/files/2023/03/8323.png)']

Categories: ['Yleinen']

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/PUNALIPPU/2023-03-01T99-00-00-04-00/8323.png)** to the streets on March 8!**

** On behalf of the class line in the female movement!**

The revolutionary movements of the Nordic countries greet the working women, the folk of oppressed peoples and all revolutionary on the 8th of the women's world. We have merged under the same flag that we are associated with our efforts to fight and resist the opposite of workers' oppression and exploitation and create a female movement.

The economic crisis has become a recession. Controlling classes and their state -owned burden on labor -class shoulders, dramatically rising prices, surgery to welfare subsidies, attacks on salaries and working conditions with a thirsty loan. This cycle of the economic crisis, followed by a recession, has been part of capitalism. This is even more in our time, since 1900, when capitalism is in its last, rotting distribution degree: imperialism. During 2022, food and energy prices have risen very rapidly. Many European countries have experienced more speed rising than 40 years. This means that the workers can buy less on our old wages. This works so that workers pay more to create new capitalist growth. Capitalists put us to pay for their crisis.

This February has passed 1 year since the Ukrainian -dedicated invasion began. Russian imperialism attacked the Ukrainian-Incredible nation, but the war began in 2014 with the presence of Crimean and Eastern Ukanrainos. This war has killed tens of thousands, and millions have become refugees. The warfare of the war is especially a racing battle between the US Jaisäjän imperialism. The Ukraine people are in a legitimate national exemption war against Russian imperialism. The war in Ukraine also influenced the economic and political situation throughout Europe.

** Heavier burdens for women in the working class and oppressed nations **This context of this crisis and imperialist war also directly influences the position of the women. Patriarchal violence has increased. Sexual approved use is on the rise, especially the exploitation of refugee women from Ukraine. War, but also prices rising and well -being, drive more women to prostitution and the so -called "sex industry". This is facilitated by the Patriarchal and recessional ideological-cultural propaganda, which is aimed at women and men. It is manifested in how it describes and sees women's bodies, women's roles in the workplace and in the family, women's sexual activity, etc. "left", and from right women are bombed by liberal enclosure policy and theory of "sex work" for taisocial conservative male civilism. Both sides are responsible for the needs ofimerialism, its special place and its rotten individualism -oriented egoism.

Imperialism implements the patriarchy and has blended it into its own economic and political structures. This is especially the touch of the third world. In recent years, the growth of violence against women has been seen throughout the world. Women in oppressed countries carrying mimpperism and patriarchate dual tanning. Imperialism deprives them, and they are tied to feudal oppression. They are the ones who pay the most payable price in the offensive and robbery war, those with the minimum assets that receive the lowest salary and have the most responsibility for families and raising children. They are the ones that are sold and bought in the despicable industry of "sex tourism". Imperialism shares the world: to the oppressive and oppressed countries. A handful of imperialists oppress the huge majority of the world's nations and peoples. In the oppressive countries, women, especially peasant and workers, are the most sophisticated and most deprived.

** We need a revolutionary female movement on the basis of a class line **Our enemy has always done everything to prevent progress. The dominant classes are just trying to drown the revolution in the blood, but they use all the open and covered method to mislead, break down the fight and organization of the people. They have legal idiots in reformists and bourgeois and bourgeois bourgeois feminists. These forces spread from thought elections, pacifism and legalism, which hold the battle in their opposite: a toothless reformist movement that acts as a useful tool for the dominant class. These forces spread paratism, which separates working -class women and men, and dash the dangerous illusion that women could be released from the air revolution. They spread postmodern identity policy, "racial theory" and šovinism, recession theories that poison the minds of the forces. Even when they appear as "feminist" or "revolutionary", these forces are old -fashioned and recession. They retain imperialism and patriarchy and defer the progress and revolution.

Women, working class and all oppressed peoples have a burning need for a revolutionary female movement in order to develop in battle for struggle to revolutionize society. This movement must be based on the class line, the workers' organizations, the poorest and the most oppressive of the poorest. The liberalization of the working class must be the work of the workers themselves, and this truth is also suitable for women. The working class is a class that releases all mankind by liberating itself. If the working class does not lead, management will flow to bourgeois and small bourgeois parties, groups and clips that objectively serve themselves, their own classroom stresses and the interests of the prevailing system. We urge work to do with working -class and revolutionary women to join the interconnection of the promotion of women's battle and organization to create a visual revolutionary women's movement.

** down the imperialist war and rising prices!**

** Aalto from Aalto, a blow against shock, imperialism and patriarchate!**

** forward toward the revolutionary female movement!**

