# Testimonies in the trial for the kidnapping of Manuel Guerra

Author: carga

Time: 2023-03-01T99:00:00-04:00

Head Description: On Wednesday 22, a new hearing was held in the so -called ABO trial (by the clandestine centers Atlético, Banco, Olimpo), in which the disappearance of Manuel “Quebracho” Guerra, Secretary of Organization of the JCR kidnapped by the dictatorship is included November 1, 1977.

Description: In this audience Mario “El Gaucho” Garelik, lawyer, who represented Manuel's companion, Teresita Castrillejo, gave testimony, in the presentation of the first habeas corpus at the time of his kidnapping. Then Claudio Balaclav, comrade of the party who shared militancy and friendship with Quebracho and Teresita, and also participates in & Hellip;

Images: ['[Facundo-Guerra-en-juicio-por-secuestro-de-Manuel-Guerra.jpg](https://pcr.org.ar/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Facundo-Guerra-en-juicio-por-secuestro-de-Manuel-Guerra.jpg)']

Type: article

<!--METADATA-->

![](Images/Partido Communista Revolucionario/2023-03-01T99-00-00-04-00/Facundo-Guerra-en-juicio-por-secuestro-de-Manuel-Guerra.jpg)In this audience Mario “El Gaucho” Garelik, lawyer, who represented Manuel's companion, Teresita Castrillejo, gave testimony, in the presentation of the first habeas corpus at the time of her kidnapping. Luegodeclaró Claudio Balaclav, comrade of the party who in those years shared Militancia and friendship with Quebracho and Teresita, and also participates in the Labor and consensus of the former clandestine detention center, torture and extermination "Club Atlético". Finally, Facundo Guerra spoke, today Secretariodel PCR of Mendoza, son of Manuel. For Wednesday 8, the Eduardo González, priest friend of the family and Ricardofierro, first JCR secretary, are planned.

#### ** The first habeas corpus **

Mario Garelik, who was legal agent of the PCR at the time of the 1976 coup, recalled that two habeas corpus were presented 48 hours after the kidnapping demanded war, one in the federal justice and another in an instructional court. Ambos were rejected by power Executive because "I was not detained." He also had that after the kidnapping, occurred in broad daylight in a Barde Las Heras and Pueyrredón in the Federal Capital, Teresita Ymanuel raided and Manuel, which was not ordered by any court. “In the AllanamientoBaron things. I knew many years after the appearance of a newspaper's impression sheet in Atlético. ”

Garelik declared, showing the period climate, which was joined with Teresita in the squares to sign the writings, and that the main objective of the habitorpus was “mainly for when one made international complaints, aorganisms such as the UN, the OAS, the Church, etc They were a constancy of Las Sebueros. Because if there was no habeas corpus, the dictatorship answered international organisms that the person "clandestinized" that is why he did not find it. " He stressed that there was an English newspaper, Buenos Aires Herald, which published the habeas corpus.

He also said that "Teresita Castrillejo and others were an example of making international organizations."

#### ** "The dictatorship could not with Quebracho" **Balaclav recounts that friends were making “and when they got married, at the end of the 75 and they did not have a weight for their party, I remember that we organized it in the center of my mother's house running all the furniture.”

Claudio highlighted the intense campaign against the coup displayed by the PCR and Lajcr, the debates with friends of other political forces that saw with good fight. He recalled that the next day of the kidnapping of Quebracho, Teresita called him telling him that he had not fell asleep that night. "After the initial confusion, we start from the base that they were kidnapped."

Balaclav took measures such as moving, changing work and leaving the studies of architecture, and stressed that in the face of torture, “we knew that they used the Genocidas to obtain information, Manuel acted firmly. The dictatorship of him with him. That is why many of us are still alive. ”

Claudio told how years later they learned of the complaint that he had made to the kidnapping of Manuel, Federico Westerkamp, who even took the number of the car's patent in which they took him, who was from a police officer.

He said that Teresita went to live in Mendoza, with her son Facundo born in November of 76, where she continued with the search and was the founder of the Mothers of Plaza de Mayo in that province.

Balaclav detailed how, in 2012, from accompanying Teresita in the labúsqueda of witnesses, it was related to members of the Athletic Labor and Consense Commission: “Touring the room where they expose objects found in the partial excavation of the site, show us a metallic plate , that I inmediably recognize as a cliché plate. Seeing it in detail, I observe the impression, among others, a PCR flag ”. He told how from Deahí an investigation began, confronting the archives of the newspaper, giving with a 1973 specimen where that photo appears, and that the archaeologists of the site, who had access to the new hour collection, made the corresponding technical commitments, and "They confirmed that the published photo in a new hour corresponded to the metal plaque found in Atlético."

This printing cliché is part of those used during every ladictor in the clandestine printing press of the party, guaranteeing the exit of the spotted periodic, and its distribution throughout the country.#### ** Facundo Guerra: “I waited 45 years to declare” **

The fellow Guerra began his statement based on what sum told about those first years of his life, in which his mother began Manuel. He rescued the solidarity of partners and family members, and how he met his father from the stories of his mother, family and comrades. "My first memories are from my mother in the organization of the mothers of Plaza de Mayo de Mendoza, eniglesias meetings to make habeas corpus, and human rights days."

Then Facundo recalled how in the 90 row".

Facundo referred to the process after the 2001 outbreak, when the trials from 2003 are. And that the situation changed from the discovery of the impression plate that appeared in Atlético, "which links my father with that place", because testimonies provided by survivors "were not considered sufficient evidence."

"This trial for us family members is very important, since it is unalucha of more than four decades," said Facundo, and questioned that it was not representative: "I would have liked to see the faces to the defendants." He claimed the investigation, and told how there are testimonies of detainees in Córdoba to those who interrogated by Manuel Guerra. That Aldueño of the car is investigated in which his father was kidnapped, and that the files are known. And he also claimed that those responsible for the first judgment of the habeas corpus were investigated, due to complicity in the kidnapping, since the moment they already had Westerkamp's complaint and did nothing.Finally, Facundo Guerra again claimed that justice progresses and accelerates work in these judgments, "because we see colleagues processed in Mendoza, Chubut, or raids with follow -ups and theotelephonic interventions to social organizations, and I do not see the same effort in these judges" and said that The need for justice is not just a problem of relatives, because the dictatorship was not only the 30 thousand missing, but 20 thousand closed factories, a fraudulent external debt whose consequences are seen until today, and 25 percent of poverty structural . Finishing today's sufferings has a lot to see with the impunity of yesterday. ”

Today N ° 1952 03/01/2023

